like org-pomodoro but with pausing and auto-start, continuous timer and WSL support (powershell)

org-pomodoro-auto-start
is set to t by default

my config, and I provided pomodoro.wav in resources if you prefer to use my alarm.

((I use load-path as this is not official package, and in case I prefer to use the vanilla package,
I can revert back to that))

----

  (add-to-list 'load-path "~/.emacs.d/site-lisp/org-pomodoro")
  (require 'org-pomodoro)

  (setq org-pomodoro-keep-killed-pomodoro-time t)
  (setq org-pomodoro-clock-break nil)
  (setq org-pomodoro-finished-sound "~/.emacs.d/site-lisp/org-pomodoro/pomodoro.wav")
  (setq org-pomodoro-finished-sound-p t)
  (setq org-pomodoro-length 25)
  (setq org-pomodoro-short-break-length 5)
  (setq org-pomodoro-long-break-length 20)
  (setq org-pomodoro-long-break-sound "~/.emacs.d/site-lisp/org-pomodoro/pomodoro.wav")
  (setq org-pomodoro-short-break-sound "~/.emacs.d/site-lisp/org-pomodoro/pomodoro.wav")
  (setq org-pomodoro-ticking-sound-p nil)

  (global-set-key (kbd "C-c p") #'org-pomodoro-toggle-pause)
  (global-set-key (kbd "C-c s") #'org-pomodoro)

  (setq org-pomodoro-auto-start t)